<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi"></span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p1"></span> <span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p1.1"></span>Canon LXXV.  (Greek lxxviii.)</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p2"></span>Of asking from the Emperors
defenders of the Churches.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p3"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p3.1"></span>On</span> account of the afflictions of
the poor by whose troubles the Church is worn out without any
intermission, it seemed good to all that the Emperors be asked to allow
defenders for them against the power of the rich to be chosen under the
supervision of the bishops.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p4"></span><span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p4.1"></span>Notes.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p5"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p5.1"></span>Ancient Epitome of Canon LXXV.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p6"></span>That the bishop be not annoyed, let
Defensors be appointed.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p7"></span>This is Canon X. of Carthage,
September, 401.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p8"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p8.1"></span>Johnson.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.lxxvi-p9"></span>See note on Can. Chalcedon, 23.

